<D>__{it is strictly for our orphans' sake that i destroy any record of their natural mothers. of course they will, one day, want to know. but orphans, especially, should look forward to their futures. not back to their pasts.}
<L>__{interior window, corridor day}
<A>__{homer sees curly standing all alone by a window in the corridor; a suitcase is next to him.}
<C>__{homer}
<D>__{hi, curly. you going somewhere?}
<A>__{curly shakes his head.}
<C>__{curly}
<D>__{i thought they might take me.}
